"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-what-to-watch-paris-olympics-august-4-noah-lyles-goes-for-first-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Day 9 of the Olympics is here, and it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s another big one.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 58, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s my daily guide to help you know what events to watch.\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should do the trick whether you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re planning to spend a full Sunday in front of the TV or just picking and choosing spots.\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can also subscribe toSports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daily Rings, my daily podcast where Dan Gartland and I are recapping the Games every night.\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999999825831766, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New episodes have been published every night before NBC\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s prime-time coverage is even over.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s what I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be watching Sunday, August 4.\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not a comprehensive list;visit Olympics.comfor a full schedule.\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All events will stream live on Peacock.\", \"from\": 609, \"to\": 648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_Records\", \"score\": 0.9893848101626759, \"rank\": 0.008772278400624074, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peacock_Records\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll also be tweeting out a schedule of medal events, Team USA games and other favorites each day.\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Day 9 Olympics viewing guide!\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully this time with no typos, but no promises.\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fun Sunday on tap#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/5G2UxDMYRQ  It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s time for the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100 meters.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Noah Lyles is the reigning world champ, though Jamaica\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Kishane Thompson is the betting favorite.\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 1044, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 944, \"end\": 954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9951653277823785, \"rank\": 0.004858159714709314, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No American man has won this event since 2004\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094of course a guy by the name of Usain Bolt was in the way for a while.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.546708384918775, \"rank\": 0.4794643869411305, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1124, \"end\": 1134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race starts at 3:50 p.m.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, and don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t tune in late because it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be over in less than 10 seconds.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The other gold medals that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be awarded during the afternoon track and field session are the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hammer throw and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s high jump.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sunday is the final round of the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s golf tournament, and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve got a great leaderboard.\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American Xander Schauffele is tied with Spain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s John Rahm for first place at 14-under.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1509, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.546708384918775, \"rank\": 0.4794643869411305, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xander Schauffele\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xander_Schauffele\"}, {\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Rahm\", \"score\": 0.9996934937443822, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Rahm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Rahm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Rahm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then Great Britain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Tommy Fleetwood is one shot behind.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1621, \"end\": 1636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll make up the final group.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"American and world No.\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.546708384918775, \"rank\": 0.4794643869411305, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1 Scottie Scheffler is in a group four shots off the lead.\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1717, \"end\": 1734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Golf begins at 3 a.m.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, but the leaders won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t go off until 6:39 a.m. and should hit the back nine in the nine o\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099clock hour.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the last day of tennis, and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve got three Olympic matches left.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see bronze and gold matches to wrap up women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doubles, with a dream matchup in between them.\\u00c2  The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles tournament has come down to Novak Djokovic vs. Carlos Alcaraz, the top two seeds in the tournament.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2135, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2154, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic has an all-time record 24 Grand Slam singles titles; he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s won everything there is to win except an Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2207, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999999576384662, \"rank\": 4.236132981854877e-08, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alcaraz has won four Grand Slams and is viewed as the next man up.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2331, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7307209063809316e-20, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tennis starts at 6 a.m. and they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be the second match on the court, followed by the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s doubles gold match.\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final day of indoor swimming (we still have marathon swimming to come) has four medal events beginning at 12:30 p.m.\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET: the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 50-meter freestyle, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 1500-meter free, and both the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 4X100 medley relays.\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In cycling, the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s road race was a fun watch Saturday morning and the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s event goes off Sunday at 8 a.m.\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 2880, \"to\": 2883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball has reached the round of 16.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sara Hughes and Kelly Cheng will face a team from Italy at 4 p.m.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2949, \"end\": 2955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"score\": 0.9999861432575555, \"rank\": 1.04387989864408e-05, \"text\": \"Hughes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howard_Hughes\"}, {\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"score\": 0.999998398935449, \"rank\": 1.601067056288587e-06, \"text\": \"Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Osbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 2994, \"end\": 2999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9962922498482418, \"rank\": 0.0037188068436341004, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 3010, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(The Nuss/Kloth team will have its round of 16 game the next day.)\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you read my post yesterday, you know how excited I am forkayak cross: Heats continue on Sunday, now with four kayaks in the water at once instead of three.\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Evy Leibfarth will be in the fifth heat of the session at 10:45 a.m.\", \"from\": 3241, \"to\": 3322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA archer Brady Ellison already won his fourth Olympic medal this week in the mixed team event.\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3328, \"end\": 3336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9995431658258875, \"rank\": 0.0004570428862717988, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3344, \"end\": 3357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brady_Ellison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brady Ellison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brady_Ellison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brady_Ellison\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has an early-morning quarterfinal in the individual competition, hoping to advance all the way to the medal matches just after 8:30 a.m.\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s basketball team continues group play against Germany at 11:15 a.m.\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3639, \"end\": 3646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9966589723655189, \"rank\": 0.0022621166077293822, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s singles table tennis medals will be awarded Sunday morning.\", \"from\": 3666, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending Olympic silver medalist Fan Zhendong will go for gold andfan-favorite 17-year-old Felix LeBrunwill compete for bronze.\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3772, \"end\": 3784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fan Zhendong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fan_Zhendong\"}, {\"begin\": 3830, \"end\": 3835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Felix_Mendelssohn\", \"score\": 0.9999996776910458, \"rank\": 2.769808644523787e-07, \"text\": \"Felix\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Felix_Mendelssohn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Felix_Mendelssohn\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Action starts at 7:30 a.m.\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, listeners of my podcast know I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll be glued to the Croatia vs. Spain men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s handball game at 3 p.m.\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 4009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3960, \"end\": 3967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999897301954502, \"rank\": 9.492915109318715e-06, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9986775342500309, \"rank\": 0.0013242162445339586, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET.\", \"from\": 4010, \"to\": 4013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one will advance out of group play.\", \"from\": 4014, \"to\": 4054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Mitch Goldich is a senior editor for Sports Illustrated, mostly focused on the NFL.\", \"from\": 4083, \"to\": 4230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4147, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"sco